<br>
There is a deep need to Beta test the new stuff, its abundantly clear that just /betabuffing people to 65 is worse than useless when it comes to actually testing the new content.  It needs to be attacked from the point of view of a cohesive group of people who know what the fuck they are doing.<br>
<br>
However if you make one guild the &quot;Beta designate&quot; then you run the risk of having one guild knowing all the l33t beta infoz (ALA Afterlife a few expansions ago) and even the perception that you had a leg-up makes everyone belittle any accomplishments in the full release.  Part of the fun inherant in the high end is to be the pioneers and the ego-boosting recognition it involves.  If that is comprimised then people dont wanna beta (hence the horrible horrible Beta testing of GoD)<br>
<br>
The solution bandied about was to have EVERYONE Beta test, but only in a limited sense.  I.E. Talisman would get invited to Beta Test a raid on Friday June 4th at 7pm PST and we'd all be copied over onto the Beta server and ready to go at that time.  We'd test the raid (probably using placeholder graphics so the ooo aaah factor wasnt removed of seeing the shit later) and then go home.  Different guilds with different raid styles and strengths could be used to test different aspects of an encounter and then following all that the thing would be set for release.  Eseentially the same basic thing that goes on now in Live, but doing it in the Beta test. If the l33t infoz are spread out and made generic then no one has any big advantage over another and parity is established.<br>
<br>
As 'compensation' for doing the testing (and thereby not doing normal raids on Live servers) there would be individual and guild based rewards for testing.  Otherwise the ones you really want to test stuff might rebel against the testing because it was cutting too deeply into their normal raiding time.  However by spreading the testing around it should require less effort for any particular person or group so it might not be too taxing on anyone.<br>
<br>
Sony seemed most sincerely apologetic about GoD and how horrible it was tested and that it was released not even remotely done.  The whole expansion was designed with level 70 in mind and the extra levels got removed and the whole thing released before that change could filter down to all the content.  This is why the whole things seemed a bit more difficult than it should have been.<br>
<br>
Lots more details from the summit will be coming out in the next few days. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://p201.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=valae>valae</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#330000>(6/6/04 12:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19472.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.cox.net/prisoner37/watcher2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Details</span><hr size=1> still didnt seem to offffer a fix for 54 people limit raids in GoD <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://members.cox.net/prisoner37/Valae-sig.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://p201.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=singsang>SingSang</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.pike-place.com/images/gifs/belain_10x10.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Minstrel</span><br>  Posts: 51<br> <font color=#330000>(6/6/04 12:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19472.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.belain.com/files/Singthumb.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Details</span><hr size=1> What I see in that post is a high focus on feature requests and little focus (albiet some) in testing and the like. I see no commentary on existing broken quests. I see no comments on progression of dealing with pathing (which has not, IMHO, gotten any better as yet. Some things are better, but for every bug fixed, another seems to appear).<br>
<br>
The fact that GoD was tuned for lvl 70, then that was pulled out and the thing still went out the door at all is seriously disgusting - explains a lot, but is downright disgusting.<br>
<br>
Relative to the whole &quot;uber vs. the comman man&quot; thing. What I see in the beta discussion is copying over of uberguild_001 from the server of the day, and little discussion of basic grouping content testing, solo testing, etc. from ANYONE, let alone someone with average rather then top guild equipment. In short, yet another facet of the &quot;Test 2% of the product&quot; problem. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=485847" target="top"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.belain.com/files/singsig.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
