<br>
when you try wholly new kinds of things (as was done for a number of the raids in GoD) then things are much less certain and you need a few real runs at it before you can balance.  Until now that &quot;Live Beta Test&quot; has been done by whoever got to the zone first.  What the above is aimed at is eliminating the need for the &quot;Live Beta Test&quot; and have shit that works out of the box.<br>
<br>
The people in attendence were broken up into focus groups to deal with different aspects.  The stuff I've posted on comes only from the focus group that Talisman was a part of : the high end raid content.  There are probably many other issues related to general content that were covered in other groups. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://p201.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=whee>whee</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Minstrel</span><br>  Posts: 639<br> <font color=#330000>(6/6/04 1:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19472.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Details</span><hr size=1> haha, if <br>
